    <stitle>STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, TILT/TELESCOPING - 2000, 4000, 8000 - MAINTENANCE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>MAINTENANCE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="pm" graphiccount="0">
            <title>END YOKE PINCH BOLTS</title>
            <para>The steering column end yoke pinch bolt assembly should be checked annually or every 50,000 miles
                (80,000 kilometers), whichever comes first.
            </para>
            <para>Visually inspect that the plastic collar has been sheared off. If the plastic collar is present,
                tighten the nut until the collar shears off. If the nut appears loose, do not tighten it further;
                install a new nut.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
